Longtime Illinois congressman Phil Crane has died of lung cancer at age 84.

The Chicago-born Republican became known as a an anti-tax crusader and pre-Reagan advocate of limited government. 

Mr Crane died Saturday night at his daughter's home in Jefferson, Maryland, surrounded by his family, a representative said. 

